    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-05-04T21:17:31+09:30" end-time-local="2026-05-04T21:17:31+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-04T11:47:31Z" end-time-utc="2026-05-04T11:47:31Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A low pressure system in Bass Strait and associated trough will clear eastwards, weakening their influence of SA by Monday evening. A ridge of high pressure will begin to extend from the west on Tuesday and will be briefly be weakened as a cold front crosses the southeast on Wednesday afternoon. The ridge will begin to re-establish in the wake of the front and stabilise over SA with the slow moving high pressure centre sitting south of WA by Friday.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW011" description="Eastern Eyre Peninsula" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-05-04T21:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-05-05T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-04T11:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-05-04T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Mostly clear. Slight chance of a shower in the south, near zero chance elsewhere. Winds southwesterly 15 to 20 km/h.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-05-05T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-05-06T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-04T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-05-05T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Medium chance of showers near the coast, slight chance elsewhere. Light winds becoming south to southwesterly 15 to 20 km/h in the morning then becoming light in the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to between 7 and 10 with daytime temperatures reaching around 20.</text>
                <text type="fire_danger">No Rating</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">##</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-05-06T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-05-07T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-05T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-05-06T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. The chance of morning fog. Medium chance of showers, most likely in the afternoon and evening. Light winds becoming west to southwesterly 15 to 25 km/h in the morning then tending south to southwesterly 25 to 35 km/h in the early afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to around 8 with daytime temperatures reaching between 18 and 21.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-05-07T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-05-08T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-06T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-05-07T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. Slight chance of a shower near the coast, near zero chance elsewhere. Winds southerly 25 to 40 km/h turning southwesterly 15 to 25 km/h during the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to between 8 and 11 with daytime temperatures reaching around 16.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="4" start-time-local="2026-05-08T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-05-09T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-07T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-05-08T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. Medium chance of showers near the coast, slight chance elsewhere. Winds southwesterly 20 to 30 km/h turning southerly 25 to 35 km/h during the day then tending south to southwesterly 15 to 20 km/h during the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to between 7 and 10 with daytime temperatures reaching around 18.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
